parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Tread Separation and Belt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and belt failure can lead to tire blowouts, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.

The inability to check the transmission fluid level can lead to premature wear and tear on the transmission, causing malfunctions and potentially resulting in costly repairs or even transmission failure.
symptoms: Unable to check transmission fluid level

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission malfunction can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: unusual noises or vibrations when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Breather Tube and Seal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank breather tube and seal can cause gasoline fumes to leak into the passenger compartment, posing a fire hazard and potential health risks to occupants. Additionally, fuel leakage to the exterior of the vehicle can lead to a fire hazard and environmental damage.
symptoms: Gasoline fumes or odors inside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Modified Fuel System Failure (Winnegabo Gas Generator)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Modifications made to the fuel system to accommodate a gas generator can lead to fuel leaks, fires, and other safety hazards, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: gasoline fumes or odors inside the vehicle
